With six weeks to go before taking the reins of The Est=C3=A9e Lauder Compa=
nies, incoming C.E.O. St=C3=A9phane de La Faverie flew to Canada the other =
day with another high-ranking executive, Nicola Kilner, to deliver some def=
lating news. Kilner, the co-founder and C.E.O. of Deciem, would be stepping=
 back from the Toronto-helmed beauty brand that she founded 11 years ago=E2=
=80=94five months after ELC finally completed its gradual, years-long acqui=
sition of her company for $1.7 billion ( https://www.elcompanies.com/en/new=
